05:39.139 --> 05:40.974
Excuse me,
Mr. McBride?

05:41.041 --> 05:42.519
- Yes, sir.
- May I talk to you
one second?

05:42.543 --> 05:43.711
Yeah, what's up?

05:46.947 --> 05:50.584
This is a bit delicate,
but I've been advised
by the family,

05:50.651 --> 05:52.419
they'd prefer you not be here.

05:52.420 --> 05:53.721
I don't think
she had any family.

05:53.787 --> 05:55.789
Well,
her sister-in-law.

05:55.856 --> 06:00.494
Well, listen, we were really
close friends with her, so...

06:00.561 --> 06:01.838
- I'm very sorry.
- Well, we just...

06:01.862 --> 06:03.230
We just want to pay our respect.

06:03.296 --> 06:04.798
I've asked you both to leave.

06:04.865 --> 06:07.200
But, you know, I mean,
we were every bit as close...

06:07.267 --> 06:08.612
probably closer than
her sister there.

06:08.636 --> 06:10.638
I'd be happy to
escort you off personally.

06:10.704 --> 06:12.440
Please don't be fooled
by the collar.

06:12.473 --> 06:15.175
The problem is
you're asking too nicely.

06:15.242 --> 06:16.577
Get the fuck out of here.

06:16.644 --> 06:18.546
You make a practice
out of threatening people

06:18.612 --> 06:19.613
at your funerals?

06:19.680 --> 06:21.248
Hang on a second.

06:21.314 --> 06:23.316
You come see me sometime.

06:23.451 --> 06:25.118
It's my card.
It's a bar.

06:25.185 --> 06:27.621
A lot better place to
whip my ass than here,
okay?

06:27.688 --> 06:28.956
I want to talk to you.

06:31.525 --> 06:35.195
Hey.
Your Aunt Rachel
was a great person,

06:35.262 --> 06:36.797
and I'm sure your dad was, too.

06:36.864 --> 06:39.667
I didn't know him,
but I just want to say
I'm sorry.

06:39.733 --> 06:40.733
Please.

06:40.768 --> 06:42.536
Yeah, I get it.
Okay?

06:52.680 --> 06:54.081
He got held in contempt
on purpose.

06:54.147 --> 06:55.315
Yeah.

06:55.382 --> 06:56.662
I'm assuming
after what happened,

06:56.717 --> 06:59.086
that the contempt thing
will go away.

06:59.152 --> 07:00.287
Uh, don't count on it.

07:00.353 --> 07:02.122
The gnome is vindictive.

07:02.189 --> 07:06.126
And if Donald wants to
twist the knife into Billy...

07:06.193 --> 07:09.497
and believe me,
he wants to twist
the knife hard...

07:09.530 --> 07:10.931
then the gnome will let him.

07:10.998 --> 07:13.000
But if Mr. Cooperman
twists the knife,

07:13.066 --> 07:14.401
it's at his own peril,

07:14.502 --> 07:20.173
because the case
isn't quashed until
the contempt is vacated.

07:20.240 --> 07:23.944
Maybe I could, um...

07:24.011 --> 07:27.515
I could walk Mr. Cooperman
through the risks.

07:27.581 --> 07:30.818
If that would help.

07:31.985 --> 07:33.587
Ambitious girl.

07:35.155 --> 07:36.524
Good for you.

07:38.325 --> 07:39.893
Careful what you wish for.

07:41.629 --> 07:44.331
No, I enjoyed my time
as chief judge.

07:44.397 --> 07:45.933
It was no picnic, believe me.

07:45.999 --> 07:48.301
You're in a good place.
Don't worry.

07:48.368 --> 07:50.203
You're still young.
You've got time.

07:50.270 --> 07:53.073
I don't feel it most mornings.

07:53.140 --> 07:55.876
It's the state court.
Has some advantages.

07:55.943 --> 07:59.246
They assigned me
a beautiful, beautiful
renovated courtroom.

07:59.312 --> 08:00.547
[clears throat]

08:00.548 --> 08:02.950
Donald.

08:03.016 --> 08:04.117
Judge Kozinski.

08:04.184 --> 08:06.654
- How are you?
- Always a pleasure.

08:06.720 --> 08:08.321
Do you know my former law clerk,

08:08.388 --> 08:09.556
Judge Keller?

08:09.557 --> 08:10.924
Hello, Rosten.

08:10.991 --> 08:13.794
Your name came up the other day.

08:13.861 --> 08:16.764
Let me think, let me think.

08:16.830 --> 08:18.999
The Borns Tech case perhaps?

08:19.066 --> 08:21.569
No, it wasn't that.

08:21.602 --> 08:23.671
Let's see.

08:23.737 --> 08:27.975
It was the Senator Judiciary
Nomination Committee.

08:28.041 --> 08:30.310
Federal bench.

08:30.377 --> 08:32.312
So many positions.

08:32.379 --> 08:34.246
Shame congress won't fill them.

08:37.618 --> 08:40.854
One day.
[chuckling]

08:40.921 --> 08:42.255
Good to see you, Alex.

08:42.322 --> 08:44.457
Always a pleasure.

08:44.592 --> 08:46.760
Judge Keller.

08:46.827 --> 08:47.827
Sir.

08:51.331 --> 08:52.700
Not very subtle.

08:54.735 --> 08:57.037
You think I should
tell someone about that?

08:57.104 --> 08:59.472
Lawyers run into judges
all the time.

08:59.607 --> 09:00.741
It's not that unusual.

09:00.808 --> 09:02.275
But I heard he
never left his office.

09:02.342 --> 09:04.277
Rumors.

09:04.344 --> 09:06.346
Brilliant lawyer, that one.

09:06.413 --> 09:08.849
Odd man.

09:08.916 --> 09:12.419
Good one to know,
though, if you want to
move up in the world.

09:12.485 --> 09:13.754
Hm.

09:16.289 --> 09:17.925
Woman: All rise.

09:17.991 --> 09:20.628
The Honorable
Rosten Keller presiding.

09:23.430 --> 09:24.765
[clears throat]

09:26.266 --> 09:28.001
- Good morning, counsel.
- Good morning.

09:30.771 --> 09:32.305
Here we are again

09:32.372 --> 09:35.809
to determine if
Mr. McBride's behavior
toward this court,

09:35.876 --> 09:37.644
and specifically toward me,

09:37.645 --> 09:40.380
rises to the level of
criminal contempt.

09:40.447 --> 09:42.049
Mr. McBride,
please rise.

09:42.115 --> 09:45.185
To sentencing?
That's efficient.

09:45.252 --> 09:47.287
The court is aware of
the tragedy that occurred

09:47.354 --> 09:48.956
after our last proceeding.

09:49.022 --> 09:52.626
My sincere condolences
to both you and
your client's family.

09:52.693 --> 09:54.094
Thank you so much.

09:54.161 --> 09:55.996
The court is also
mindful of the fact

09:56.063 --> 09:59.066
that Mr. McBride
faces charges of drunk driving,

09:59.132 --> 10:00.968
and resisting arrest
in another courtroom.

10:01.034 --> 10:02.569
Yeah, good news travels fast.

10:02.636 --> 10:05.072
Would you like to
contribute to my
defense fund?

10:05.138 --> 10:08.008
In light of the circumstances,

10:08.075 --> 10:10.944
I've decided to vacate
my contempt finding.

10:11.011 --> 10:13.280
Well, that's very
compassionate of you,
your honor,

10:13.346 --> 10:16.516
but I'd like to have
my hearing just the same.

10:16.583 --> 10:19.319
I'd like to call
Donald Cooperman
to the stand, please.

10:19.386 --> 10:21.088
Hm.

10:21.154 --> 10:22.555
The contempt order is vacated.

10:22.622 --> 10:24.524
Any hearing would therefore
would be moot.

10:24.591 --> 10:26.626
Sorry, Mr. McBride.

10:26.694 --> 10:27.771
We're not playing
any games today.

10:27.795 --> 10:28.962
I don't have time.

10:29.029 --> 10:31.064
I... I think
you should make time.

10:31.131 --> 10:32.966
I'd like to redeem my good name

10:33.033 --> 10:35.903
in the same forum
where is was so
radically impugned.

10:35.969 --> 10:38.105
That's very clever.

10:38.171 --> 10:39.606
Seeking to use this proceeding

10:39.673 --> 10:41.574
as a means to dig up evidence

10:41.641 --> 10:43.576
in support of a baseless claim.

10:43.643 --> 10:45.445
The matter is adjourned.

10:45.512 --> 10:46.714
Don't be an asshole.

10:52.285 --> 10:54.454
The case is dismissed.

10:54.521 --> 10:57.190
I do wish you health,

10:57.257 --> 10:58.892
and happiness.

11:01.762 --> 11:04.998
I hope your nuts fall off,
you prick.

11:12.740 --> 11:15.108
What's up, Jason?

11:15.175 --> 11:17.477
Hey, I called your office
after the funeral.

11:17.544 --> 11:20.047
And the lady said that
you'd be here,

11:20.113 --> 11:22.015
or at the bar.

11:22.082 --> 11:23.951
Yeah. What's up, man?

11:24.017 --> 11:26.053
Well, my dad
didn't kill himself.

11:26.119 --> 11:28.822
And my Aunt Rachel said
that you knew that.

11:28.889 --> 11:30.757
Yeah, well, I'm...
I'm not for sure,

11:30.758 --> 11:33.060
but I got my suspicions.

11:33.126 --> 11:34.627
Your Aunt Rachel
was pretty convinced

11:34.762 --> 11:36.229
he wouldn't
kill himself, either.

11:36.296 --> 11:38.899
What did... What did
your mom tell you?

11:38.966 --> 11:41.768
She won't talk about it.

11:41.769 --> 11:45.305
And if he was planning on
killing himself,

11:45.372 --> 11:46.907
he would have said goodbye.

11:46.974 --> 11:48.575
Or something.

11:48.641 --> 11:51.211
Is there any way
that we could
talk to you sometime,

11:51.278 --> 11:53.646
and your mother
wouldn't know about it?

11:53.781 --> 11:55.515
Yes.

11:55.582 --> 11:57.484
Yeah.

11:57.550 --> 11:58.786
Look, that's my card.

12:01.021 --> 12:02.790
There's a number on there.

12:02.856 --> 12:04.657
It's my number,
it's in handwriting.

12:04.792 --> 12:06.794
- Okay?
- Okay.

12:06.860 --> 12:08.361
Don't show that card to anybody.

12:16.503 --> 12:18.105
What are you doing?

12:18.171 --> 12:20.941
You cannot talk to a child
without his mother present.

12:21.008 --> 12:23.710
No, you were talking to him.
I wasn't talking to him.

12:23.811 --> 12:26.046
And if anybody asks you,
that's the deal, okay?

12:26.113 --> 12:27.347
What?

12:27.414 --> 12:29.282
Trust me,
it's a good thing.
Come on.

12:29.349 --> 12:31.027
Patty: He's a kid.
He doesn't even
have capacity

12:31.051 --> 12:32.252
to bring a lawsuit.

12:32.319 --> 12:33.720
Billy: We'll file
an application

12:33.821 --> 12:35.455
for appointment as
guardian ad litem.

12:35.522 --> 12:37.724
You can be his lawyer
and get appointed by
the court.

12:37.825 --> 12:39.626
Oh, right, the mother's
gonna let that happen.

12:39.692 --> 12:41.061
It's not up to her.

12:41.128 --> 12:43.096
The court is never gonna
appoint me guardian,

12:43.163 --> 12:44.965
I have a conflict of interest.

12:45.032 --> 12:47.234
No, I have
a conflict of interest.

12:47.300 --> 12:48.168
You don't.

12:48.235 --> 12:49.837
And remember, we're not a firm.

12:49.870 --> 12:51.214
Yeah, but it doesn't matter
if we're...

12:51.238 --> 12:53.106
You know what?
You want to keep
arguing with me

12:53.173 --> 12:55.275
- all fuckin' day long,
because I can do it.
- Whoa.

12:55.342 --> 12:57.744
I am so goddamn tired
of you yappin',

12:57.845 --> 12:59.079
and fuckin' openin' your trap

12:59.146 --> 13:00.623
every fuckin' time
I have anything to say.

13:00.647 --> 13:03.083
- Take it easy.
- I'm not gonna
take it easy.

13:03.150 --> 13:04.193
I actually know what I'm doing.

13:04.217 --> 13:06.153
When are you gonna realize that?

13:06.219 --> 13:08.655
I'm gonna find out
what kind of dark ass shit's
goin' on here.

13:08.721 --> 13:11.558
We do have a dead friend.
Remember that?

13:11.624 --> 13:13.493
So you in or out?

13:27.607 --> 13:28.909
Hey, asshole.

13:31.611 --> 13:32.980
Remember me?

13:33.046 --> 13:35.983
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

13:36.049 --> 13:37.326
Why don't you take
a swing at me?

13:37.350 --> 13:39.286
I'd love to sue you
for something.

13:39.352 --> 13:41.197
You're lucky
I didn't shoot you and
your fuckin' daughter.

13:41.221 --> 13:44.892
Hey, watch your goddamn
mouth about my daughter.

13:44.958 --> 13:47.560
Who put you up to that shit?

13:47.627 --> 13:48.895
Take a walk.

13:48.896 --> 13:50.330
You may be a fuckin' tough guy,

13:50.397 --> 13:51.598
but I'm a crazy guy.

13:51.664 --> 13:54.034
The difference is
crazy guys don't give up.

13:54.101 --> 13:55.768
- Is that right?
- Yeah, that's right.

13:55.903 --> 13:57.370
So keep that in mind.

13:57.437 --> 13:58.906
I'll be waiting.

13:58.939 --> 14:00.373
I don't give up.

14:30.403 --> 14:32.505
[water running]

14:41.681 --> 14:43.616
Esperanza?

14:43.683 --> 14:46.486
Esperanza?

14:46.553 --> 14:47.787
What the hell?

14:47.854 --> 14:51.091
How'd you get in here?

14:51.158 --> 14:53.360
I told her I had permission.
Don't be mad at her.

14:53.426 --> 14:55.963
You look like shit.
What's goin' on?

14:55.996 --> 14:59.766
I went to a party, um, in Vegas.

14:59.832 --> 15:01.434
Private jet.

15:01.501 --> 15:03.003
I just got back.

15:06.806 --> 15:09.642
I did too much...
too much shit.

15:13.246 --> 15:15.448
- [groans]
- Sit down, sit down.

15:15.515 --> 15:17.484
I don't feel good.

15:17.550 --> 15:19.152
Yeah, I guess not.

16:00.760 --> 16:02.595
[sighs]
Goddamnit.

16:07.400 --> 16:09.936
Brittany, get up.
Come on, let's get up.

16:10.037 --> 16:11.771
- Brittany.
- Get off me.

16:11.838 --> 16:12.915
Don't be goin' to sleep, okay?

16:12.939 --> 16:14.707
I'm not sleeping.

16:14.774 --> 16:17.044
Well, get up.
Here, we're gonna
walk around a little bit.

16:17.077 --> 16:18.878
- Billy, get off of me.
- Come here, sweetie.

16:18.945 --> 16:20.413
Get up.
Goddamnit, get up.

16:20.480 --> 16:22.782
Get off.
Stop yelling at me.

16:22.849 --> 16:24.493
- [sighs]
- Just walk around
a minute, okay?

16:24.517 --> 16:26.519
- Okay, okay.
- Okay.

16:26.586 --> 16:28.054
Come on, let's go.

16:28.055 --> 16:29.256
Are you mad at me?

16:29.322 --> 16:30.757
No, I'm not mad at you, sweetie,

16:30.823 --> 16:32.292
I'm tryin' to help you, this...

16:32.359 --> 16:33.826
Please don't be mad at me.

16:33.893 --> 16:35.928
Just eat it all.
It'll help you.

16:36.063 --> 16:37.164
[sighs]

16:43.070 --> 16:44.204
[belching]

16:46.773 --> 16:49.742
Uh...

16:49.809 --> 16:52.745
Well, we almost got married.

16:52.812 --> 16:53.980
[chuckling]

16:54.081 --> 16:56.083
You what?

16:56.149 --> 16:58.285
- You got married?
- Forget it.

17:00.387 --> 17:02.089
Oh, shit.
Where's my purse?

17:02.122 --> 17:03.423
It's at the motel.

17:03.490 --> 17:05.625
Oh, God, I have, like,
$10,000 in there.

17:06.858 --> 17:07.960
Got it right here.

17:08.095 --> 17:09.896
You have the rest of my stuff?

17:09.962 --> 17:11.397
- Your stuff?
- The...

17:11.464 --> 17:12.974
- With the rest of my stuff?
- What, your lipstick?

17:12.999 --> 17:14.310
Yeah, I know what
you're talkin' about.

17:14.334 --> 17:15.694
There's not very much
of that left.

17:15.734 --> 17:17.770
That's why you're
in this shape. Remember?

17:17.837 --> 17:19.106
Like you're so perfect.

17:19.138 --> 17:21.508
You have a drink at this bar
three times a day.

17:21.574 --> 17:24.411
Well, how many times
have you had to fuckin',

17:24.477 --> 17:26.846
you know,
walk me over here to
eat a loaf of bread?

17:26.913 --> 17:28.915
I mean, I remember that.

17:28.981 --> 17:30.350
I can take care of myself.

17:30.417 --> 17:33.320
I'm just trying to make it work.

17:33.386 --> 17:35.688
All right,
like everybody does.
All right?

17:37.424 --> 17:39.126
Yeah, look,
I can maybe get some money,

17:39.192 --> 17:42.129
you know,
start someplace fresh, maybe.

17:42.195 --> 17:45.398
Why do you care anyway?

17:45.465 --> 17:47.600
I'm doing my job, right?

17:48.801 --> 17:50.237
Yeah, you're doin' your job.

17:50.303 --> 17:51.838
I'm not worried about your work,

17:51.904 --> 17:53.140
your work's fine.

17:56.676 --> 17:58.578
It's your personal life
I'm worried about,

17:58.645 --> 18:00.513
'cause I actually do care,
just so you know.

18:00.580 --> 18:03.683
I don't have
a personal life, Billy.

18:06.953 --> 18:09.156
I can't afford one.

18:12.859 --> 18:14.594
