Thank you so much.

34:36.908 --> 34:41.480
[whispering]
Um, take the
motherfucking deal.

34:43.882 --> 34:45.150
- No.
- Yes.

34:45.150 --> 34:47.585
So you're working freelance now?

34:47.652 --> 34:50.621
Because Wendell Corey
and Cooperman made it
very clear

34:50.688 --> 34:51.556
that we're not settling.

34:51.623 --> 34:54.659
I'm the fucking general counsel.

34:56.395 --> 35:00.366
- The offer's 500,000.
- And the offer is rejected.

35:02.000 --> 35:06.672
I am offering both sides
the opportunity to blink.

35:13.078 --> 35:15.181
Okay.

35:15.214 --> 35:18.083
Here's how it's
gonna go from here.

35:18.184 --> 35:19.685
We'll reconvene tomorrow.

35:19.751 --> 35:21.287
Yet again.

35:21.353 --> 35:22.688
You make me an offer of proof

35:22.754 --> 35:24.656
that rises considerably above

35:24.723 --> 35:26.692
this piece of shit complaint

35:26.758 --> 35:29.995
or I dismiss your
cause of action altogether.

35:30.061 --> 35:33.299
Now, I suppose you think
I can't do that.

35:34.566 --> 35:36.635
Jesus, you blew off
half a million dollars.

35:36.702 --> 35:38.946
- A half a million dollars...
- I mean, do you know
how fucked up that is?

35:38.970 --> 35:41.090
That's not shit to these guys.
Do you understand that?

35:41.207 --> 35:42.073
They're flippin' us a nickel.

35:42.208 --> 35:43.342
God.

35:43.409 --> 35:44.419
There's a hell of a lot
more to it

35:44.443 --> 35:45.577
than a half million dollars.

35:45.644 --> 35:48.214
They're hiding
something big here.

35:48.247 --> 35:50.482
There's no fucking
question about it.

35:50.549 --> 35:51.659
Don't you want to do this
for Rachel and the kid?

35:51.683 --> 35:53.219
You want to find out the truth?

35:53.285 --> 35:54.853
Oh, like you're so
fucking principled.

35:54.920 --> 35:57.856
♫♫

36:04.263 --> 36:08.434
♫ Been reckless so long ♫

36:08.500 --> 36:13.038
♫ Just a system
but you're wrong ♫

36:13.104 --> 36:17.509
♫ Future's stretched out
like a rubber check ♫

36:17.576 --> 36:21.947
♫ Don't be dippin' at
the side of your neck ♫

36:22.013 --> 36:24.950
♫♫

36:38.264 --> 36:40.599
Wendy, I'm home.

36:40.666 --> 36:42.301
What the fuck do you want, pal?

36:44.636 --> 36:47.272
You know, I like to fish myself.

36:47.273 --> 36:48.740
I catch and release, though.

36:48.807 --> 36:51.610
You ever do that,
catch and release?

36:51.677 --> 36:53.312
Drag the bastard around
by the lip

36:53.379 --> 36:55.647
'til he gets all gassed up
with lactic acid,

36:55.714 --> 36:57.559
then you take the hook out,
look him in the eye,

36:57.583 --> 36:59.418
and say,
"I was just fuckin'
with you, buddy."

36:59.485 --> 37:00.919
Man, get the fuck out of here.

37:02.921 --> 37:06.492
My client's boat blew up
in close proximity
to another boat,

37:06.558 --> 37:10.195
which is your boat.
You think I'm goin' away?

37:10.296 --> 37:11.697
Don't be stupid.

37:11.763 --> 37:13.499
I got a whole bag
full of tricks,

37:13.565 --> 37:16.201
extortion, blackmail,
all kinds of shit.

37:16.302 --> 37:17.569
Whatever it takes.

37:19.905 --> 37:21.740
Why don't you just
tell me what you know,

37:21.807 --> 37:23.442
and I'll be nice.

37:23.509 --> 37:26.378
I might even help you
with your immigration issues.

37:26.445 --> 37:28.179
What immigration issues?

37:28.314 --> 37:30.315
The ones that'll come up
if I tell the police

37:30.316 --> 37:32.318
that Gabriel's
blowing seals up again.

37:36.688 --> 37:40.692
Man. I ain't sayin' shit
'cause I don't know shit.

37:41.527 --> 37:44.496
All I know is what I saw.

37:51.069 --> 37:52.604
[explosions]

37:52.671 --> 37:55.907
Shit.
He took that
with his phone?

37:55.974 --> 37:57.343
Yeah, from a distance.

37:57.409 --> 37:59.177
Are they terrorists?

37:59.244 --> 38:01.747
I read once they
clamped down on
the Somali pirates,

38:01.813 --> 38:04.349
a lot of them ended up
here as fishermen.

38:04.350 --> 38:06.918
Marva, could you give us
a minute, please?

38:06.985 --> 38:08.554
Certainly.

38:08.620 --> 38:11.957
The Marquez boys told me
that this rained down on them
after the explosion,

38:12.023 --> 38:14.860
but, uh, it's not
the same kind of plastic
you'd get from a boat.

38:14.926 --> 38:16.628
Where's it from?

38:16.695 --> 38:19.431
I don't know.
We're gonna have to hire
an explosives expert.

38:19.498 --> 38:20.999
Who pays for that?

38:21.066 --> 38:24.536
How's that list of ex
Borns Tech employees going?

38:24.603 --> 38:27.573
Here is a list of former
Borns Tech engineers,

38:27.639 --> 38:30.376
who are registered
for the job expo.

38:30.442 --> 38:31.777
What job expo is that?

38:31.843 --> 38:34.045
Oh, the one I advertised online.

38:34.112 --> 38:37.683
It's totally free.
You just say that you're
a start up sub contractor

38:37.749 --> 38:39.217
interested in hiring somebody

38:39.284 --> 38:41.487
who has a background
in aerospace

38:41.553 --> 38:43.021
or military projects,

38:43.088 --> 38:45.457
preferably somebody with
experience at Borns Tech,

38:45.524 --> 38:47.058
and they send you
a list of names.

38:47.125 --> 38:48.560
Oh, I highlighted the ones there

38:48.627 --> 38:50.862
that left under
questionable circumstances.

38:50.929 --> 38:54.566
You know how
grumpy former employees
tend to be Chatty Cathys.

38:54.633 --> 38:56.668
- And you came up with this.
- I did.

38:56.735 --> 38:58.269
That's pretty impressive.

38:58.404 --> 39:00.105
Thank you.

39:00.171 --> 39:02.574
Okay. So, Brittany,
get an IT guy

39:02.641 --> 39:03.909
to blow these images up,

39:03.975 --> 39:05.687
and then all three of you
go through this list,

39:05.711 --> 39:07.979
and find somebody that
knows what this shit is.

39:08.046 --> 39:09.657
You don't think the video
would be enough?

39:09.681 --> 39:11.950
With this judge?
No, I don't.

39:13.318 --> 39:16.087
Letts: Look, I did what
any good lawyer would do.

39:16.154 --> 39:17.689
We can afford to settle this.

39:17.756 --> 39:19.458
No, Leonard, we cannot.

39:19.525 --> 39:23.028
You know what
the biggest lie in
American history is?

39:23.094 --> 39:26.598
That if Richard Nixon
had just admitted
what he did,

39:26.665 --> 39:29.768
he wouldn't have had to resign.

39:29.835 --> 39:31.603
That's bullshit.

39:31.670 --> 39:33.805
If he'd told the truth
about Watergate,

39:33.872 --> 39:36.608
they'd have just
kept on digging.

39:36.675 --> 39:40.546
He'd have gone
to prison or worse.

39:40.612 --> 39:42.714
What are you
not telling me, Wendell?

39:42.781 --> 39:44.516
What the hell is going on here?

39:46.818 --> 39:48.162
Now, I took this job
on the promise that

39:48.186 --> 39:49.855
there were no issues here.

39:49.921 --> 39:53.925
I moved my family here.
Now you're telling me
there are issues.

39:57.362 --> 39:59.498
Leonard, there are
always issues.

39:59.565 --> 40:03.101
And I've been trying to
protect you from them,
but you won't let me.

40:03.168 --> 40:06.171
And there's not
enough money in the world

40:06.237 --> 40:09.174
to settle this case.

40:09.240 --> 40:12.744
So just make sure
it goes the hell away.

40:24.490 --> 40:26.692
Hey.
Case over?

40:26.758 --> 40:28.326
No.

40:28.393 --> 40:30.562
Judge designated it complex.

40:30.629 --> 40:33.932
[chuckles]
Billy needs to make a
compelling offer of proof

40:33.999 --> 40:36.568
by tomorrow,
which should be difficult.

40:36.635 --> 40:38.136
It'll probably go away.

40:38.203 --> 40:41.607
Although, clearly,
your ex husband
is not about to.

40:41.673 --> 40:42.874
I tried to tell you that.

40:44.109 --> 40:47.278
Listen, if this case
survives tomorrow,

40:47.345 --> 40:50.181
and it shouldn't,
but if it does,

40:50.248 --> 40:53.985
my marching orders
are not gonna be to
merely argue the case.

40:54.052 --> 40:57.523
They are going to be to
destroy the man bringing it.

40:57.556 --> 40:59.290
And I...

40:59.357 --> 41:00.792
I don't want to pretend to you

41:00.859 --> 41:03.762
that it's not gonna get ugly.

41:03.829 --> 41:07.232
I hear ya,
but has it not
gotten ugly already?

41:07.298 --> 41:09.400
The last plaintiff is dead.

41:09.535 --> 41:11.536
Don't be ridiculous.

41:11.537 --> 41:13.539
That was an accident.

41:13.572 --> 41:15.306
I know.
I checked with the LAPD,

41:15.373 --> 41:17.843
they said they had
a couple of tips,
but no real leads.

41:17.909 --> 41:19.678
You checked?

41:20.311 --> 41:21.613
I was curious.

41:21.680 --> 41:23.982
Billy's making you crazy again.

41:24.049 --> 41:25.551
- Come on.
- This is what happens.

41:25.584 --> 41:28.253
Whenever you spend
any length of time with him,

41:28.319 --> 41:30.121
you catch his crazy.

41:30.188 --> 41:31.657
It's true.

41:31.723 --> 41:34.993
Can I ask you a question?

41:35.060 --> 41:38.229
Why do you think
that you were selected
for this case?

41:39.598 --> 41:41.032
You'd have to ask Cooperman.

41:41.099 --> 41:43.802
No, I'm asking you.

41:43.869 --> 41:48.840
Donald clearly thinks you
match up well against Billy.

41:48.907 --> 41:50.876
Do you two match up well?

41:50.942 --> 41:52.177
What?

41:52.243 --> 41:54.179
Well, I didn't fuck him,
if that's what you mean.

41:54.245 --> 41:57.115
No, that's not... What?

41:57.182 --> 41:59.284
Jesus Christ.

41:59.350 --> 42:00.752
You know, after all these years,

42:00.819 --> 42:02.854
after everything
he put you through,

42:02.921 --> 42:05.791
you are still obsessed with him.

42:05.857 --> 42:07.325
- Hey...
- It's just sad.

42:07.392 --> 42:08.760
I did not mean to offend you.

42:08.827 --> 42:10.696
- [sighs]
- Callie...

42:10.762 --> 42:13.298
You know, not everyone
who meets him

42:13.364 --> 42:14.600
wants to fuck him.

42:14.633 --> 42:16.067
That's your problem, Michelle.

42:16.134 --> 42:18.303
And I tell you this
as your friend.

42:18.369 --> 42:19.905
Get over it.

42:23.875 --> 42:26.477
We're... we're seeking out
Borns Tech personnel,

42:26.612 --> 42:31.016
because they
pre-qualify for, uh...
for security clearances.

42:31.082 --> 42:33.084
Yes, we manufacture components

42:33.151 --> 42:35.954
for small private
weapons companies.

42:36.021 --> 42:39.524
Uh, lasers.
Directional components.

42:39.625 --> 42:41.059
It is for a management position.

42:41.126 --> 42:43.494
It's for a
senior management
mid level.

42:43.629 --> 42:44.839
Well, I know it's a big company,

42:44.863 --> 42:46.183
but, uh, the older
white engineers

42:46.231 --> 42:48.466
tend to stick together
in cliques, right?

42:48.533 --> 42:52.738
We're looking for people
specialized in flight based
classified patents.

42:52.804 --> 42:54.472
Yes, health insurance
is included.

42:54.640 --> 42:56.007
Yep, we have dental.

42:56.074 --> 42:57.985
You want to bring your pet,
you can bring your pet.

42:58.009 --> 43:02.313
Oh, I love a missile man.
[chuckles]

43:02.380 --> 43:05.751
♫♫[rock]

43:07.085 --> 43:09.220
- Hey, guess what.
- What's up? What?

43:09.287 --> 43:10.321
I think we found our guy.

43:10.388 --> 43:12.157
- Really?
- Yep.

43:12.223 --> 43:15.460
He lives out in Reseda,
and he sounds really good
on the phone.

43:15.526 --> 43:17.028
Well, let's go.

43:17.095 --> 43:17.929
Now?

43:17.996 --> 43:19.698
Of course now.
You heard the judge.

43:19.765 --> 43:21.275
If we don't have
something tomorrow,
we're fucked,

43:21.299 --> 43:23.534
so let's go.
Come on.

43:23.669 --> 43:26.071
Man.

43:26.137 --> 43:28.306
I inherited the place
from my folks,

43:28.373 --> 43:30.842
so there's no mortgage,
but there's upkeep,

43:30.909 --> 43:32.349
so there's cost.
Kind of a money pit.

43:32.377 --> 43:33.737
Did you want ice?
I don't have any.

43:33.779 --> 43:36.047
- No, I'm good.
- Thank you.

43:44.455 --> 43:48.293
So, I'm getting that
this isn't really about
a job interview.

43:48.359 --> 43:49.728
I'm an intuitive person.

43:49.795 --> 43:52.363
You're not really here
to hire me, are you?

43:52.430 --> 43:53.699
- Well...
- No.

43:53.765 --> 43:57.903
Uh, we're liars by trade,
we practice law.

43:59.370 --> 44:01.506
- This about Borns Tech?
- Billy: Yes, sir.

44:01.572 --> 44:03.441
Patty:
Which... which I said
over the phone.

44:03.508 --> 44:05.977
Remember, I wanted to
talk to you about your
employment?

44:06.044 --> 44:08.346
Yes, for the purposes
of hiring me.

44:08.413 --> 44:12.617
Yeah, and also to identify
some plastic materials.

44:12.718 --> 44:14.552
Why'd you leave there?

44:14.619 --> 44:17.122
Partly downsizing.

44:17.188 --> 44:19.758
Military cuts,
fewer weapons development,

44:19.825 --> 44:22.593
and then I had some issues
with management.

44:22.728 --> 44:23.594
What kind of issues?

44:23.729 --> 44:25.363
Psychiatric, caused by them.

44:25.430 --> 44:28.166
I am not a crazy person.
That is a stressful place.

44:28.233 --> 44:30.235
- They induce things.
- Right.

44:30.301 --> 44:31.302
I hear ya.

44:33.839 --> 44:35.406
Why don't you just
show me this plastic.

44:35.473 --> 44:36.473
Yeah.

44:47.085 --> 44:50.055
I saw your kiddie pool
out front there.

44:50.121 --> 44:51.957
Do you got some children
around here?

44:52.023 --> 44:54.760
No. Mine from when
I was a kid.

44:54.793 --> 44:56.137
Now I just use it
to catch rain water.

44:56.161 --> 44:57.362
You know, there's a drought.

44:57.428 --> 44:58.764
Right.

45:02.300 --> 45:04.202
I know what this is.

45:04.269 --> 45:06.304
What is it?

45:06.371 --> 45:07.505
I can't tell you.

45:07.572 --> 45:08.807
Patty: Why not?

45:08.874 --> 45:11.442
This is part of
a classified project.

45:11.509 --> 45:12.978
You shouldn't have it.

45:13.044 --> 45:15.080
It is a crime
for you to have this.

45:15.146 --> 45:17.682
Well, we didn't
steal it or anything,
we found it in the ocean.

45:17.783 --> 45:20.027
Well, if that's the case,
somebody at Borns Tech
is in a lot of trouble.

45:20.051 --> 45:21.987
You see, that plastic's
part of a program

45:22.053 --> 45:24.198
to test something that
isn't supposed to be
near anyplace

45:24.222 --> 45:26.224
where there are people or
really any living thing.

45:26.291 --> 45:28.059
Okay?

45:28.126 --> 45:30.796
I know.
I worked on that project.

45:30.862 --> 45:31.797
What project?

45:31.863 --> 45:35.133
I can't tell you that.

45:35.200 --> 45:37.402
Right, you keep saying that.

45:37.468 --> 45:39.871
You know, Ned,
we can pay you as
an expert witness,

45:39.938 --> 45:44.142
and maybe help you defray
some of these upkeep costs
you were talking about.

45:44.209 --> 45:46.477
- How much?
- We'll talk about that
later.

45:46.544 --> 45:50.715
Why don't you just tell us
exactly what this stuff is.

45:50.816 --> 45:51.983
It's casing.

45:52.050 --> 45:53.852
For ignition housing.

45:53.919 --> 45:55.186
Ignition housing.

45:55.253 --> 45:57.555
Bombs.

45:57.622 --> 45:59.324
Very big bombs.

45:59.390 --> 46:02.393
Rocket fueled,
laser guided
badass bombs.

46:02.460 --> 46:06.832
That shit
should never have been
near any fishing boat.

46:06.898 --> 46:09.334
Can I get you to say that
in affidavit form?

46:09.400 --> 46:11.937
Absolutely not.
This is a very big company.

46:12.003 --> 46:13.304
They can hurt people.

46:13.371 --> 46:17.042
We have legal mechanisms
to conceal your identity.

46:17.108 --> 46:18.820
If you're worried about
your personal safety,

46:18.844 --> 46:19.844
don't worry about that.

46:19.845 --> 46:22.213
[groans]

46:22.280 --> 46:24.115
[stammering]

46:24.182 --> 46:25.984
Could you stop that, please?

46:27.485 --> 46:30.088
I'm... I'm sorry,
what did... what did I do?

46:30.155 --> 46:31.933
You know what you're doing.
I want you to stop.

46:31.957 --> 46:33.624
What did she do?

46:33.691 --> 46:35.326
She's putting thoughts
into my head.

46:35.393 --> 46:36.862
She's sending them
through her eyes.

46:36.928 --> 46:39.197
And I want you to stop.

46:40.966 --> 46:42.500
Stop it, Patty, okay?

46:45.036 --> 46:47.105
She won't do it again,
Ned, don't worry.

46:53.011 --> 46:55.746
So, what's the plan?

46:55.881 --> 46:57.682
Is there a plan?
What are we going to do?

46:57.748 --> 46:58.984
'Cause if the case goes on...

46:59.050 --> 47:02.753
Judge Keller is
sympathetic to us.

47:02.888 --> 47:06.391
He will close them down
for good.

47:06.457 --> 47:07.457
Trust me.

47:10.228 --> 47:13.631
Is it so difficult
to trust me, Leonard?

47:13.698 --> 47:15.433
[clicker clicking]

47:16.935 --> 47:18.769
[sighs]
Whether or not I trust you,

47:18.904 --> 47:20.905
letting Billy McBride
rattle cages

47:20.906 --> 47:23.374
is... is like giving
a lunatic a hammer,

47:23.441 --> 47:25.043
and letting him
run through Tiffany's.

47:25.110 --> 47:26.444
That man is dangerous.

47:28.679 --> 47:30.148
But I'm more so.

47:31.950 --> 47:33.118
[clicker clicking]

47:42.928 --> 47:44.595
You asleep?

47:44.662 --> 47:46.131
Not even close.

47:49.300 --> 47:50.301
Nervous?

47:53.939 --> 47:55.941
Yeah, yeah, I'm nervous.

48:05.583 --> 48:06.583
Hey.

48:08.686 --> 48:10.989
It's like riding a bike.

48:11.056 --> 48:13.624
You walk into that
judge's chamber,

48:13.691 --> 48:17.028
you become Billy McBride again.

48:17.095 --> 48:19.164
You wait and see.

48:28.539 --> 48:29.975
How about I relax you?

48:35.446 --> 48:36.446
No.

48:36.481 --> 48:38.116
You sure?

48:43.254 --> 48:45.790
One of these days.

48:45.856 --> 48:47.492
[chuckles]

48:54.465 --> 48:55.465
Come here.

49:04.509 --> 49:05.576
[sighs]

49:09.580 --> 49:11.516
[seagulls squawking]

49:14.185 --> 49:16.321
[traffic noise]

49:25.563 --> 49:28.433
Jeez.
Join the crowd, honey.

49:32.037 --> 49:33.138
Excuse me.

49:33.204 --> 49:35.673
I'm going to court, sweetie.

49:35.740 --> 49:37.508
It's no place you want to be.

49:37.575 --> 49:40.645
No place you want to be.
I'll see you later. Okay?

49:46.251 --> 49:47.618
What's wrong, Billy?

49:49.054 --> 49:50.588
You look nervous.

49:50.655 --> 49:52.423
Oh, I'm not nervous,
I'm just tired.

49:52.490 --> 49:55.360
I was up all night
preparing to whip your ass.

49:56.694 --> 49:57.995
[door opens]

49:59.530 --> 50:03.068
Okay, Mr. McBride.
This is your show.

50:03.134 --> 50:04.735
What have you got?

50:04.802 --> 50:06.771
No idle chitchat first?

50:06.837 --> 50:08.506
You have 20 minutes, sir.

50:08.573 --> 50:11.342
Okay. I'll try to do it
in about five.

50:17.748 --> 50:20.751
This is the affidavit
of Ryan Larsen's son,

50:20.818 --> 50:23.788
declaring his opinion
that this was no suicide.

50:23.854 --> 50:28.326
This is my personal affidavit
of conversations I had
with eyewitnesses

50:28.393 --> 50:31.028
who say that this explosion
was a helluva lot bigger,

50:31.096 --> 50:32.673
and a helluva lot worse
than what would happen

50:32.697 --> 50:35.533
if you dropped a match
into a fuel tank of a boat.

50:35.600 --> 50:39.237
Now, this one right here
contains all of the anecdotal

50:39.304 --> 50:41.439
physical and
testimonial evidence

50:41.506 --> 50:44.375
introduced or alleged
by anyone who supports

